docs.abstract: With businesses and personal finances hit hard by a loss of income, the first of the month may mean triage in deciding what to pay.
docs.snippet: With businesses and personal finances hit hard by a loss of income, the first of the month may mean triage in deciding what to pay.
docs.lead_paragraph: On Wednesday, as on the first day of any month, many companies and households will have bills to pay. This time, a lot will simply pile up.

headline.main: April Bills Loom. The Economy Hangs on How Many Are Left Unpaid.
headline.print_headline: Hard Decisions For Americans As Bills Roll In

docs.abstract: The stimulus package includes more than $370 billion in government-backed bank loans that, in some cases, borrowers won’t have to repay.

docs.lead_paragraph: Every day counts for Glynis Donnelly, who owns a jewelry store in Tampa, Fla. Ever since the coronavirus outbreak decimated foot traffic to her store, she has been using her savings to pay her eight part-time employees.

headline.main: Small Businesses Will Get Help Paying Workers, if They Can Wait

docs.abstract: Corporations are saving cash, cutting costs and refinancing debt to manage the economic fallout of the coronavirus. Restructuring and bankruptcy experts are already getting calls.
docs.snippet: Corporations are saving cash, cutting costs and refinancing debt to manage the economic fallout of the coronavirus. Restructuring and bankruptcy experts are already getting calls.
docs.lead_paragraph: Freedom Mortgage, one of the nation’s largest mortgage lenders, is looking for additional financing as millions of homeowners are expected to stop making mortgage payments. The Cheesecake Factory said this past week it wouldn’t be able to make rent payments on its leases because of lost business. And giant companies from Kraft Heinz to Ford have tapped billions of dollars in credit from banks in preparation for an uncertain future.

headline.main: Scary Times for U.S. Companies Spell Boom for Restructuring Advisers
headline.print_headline: Panic Fuels Rush to Call Restructuring Advisers

docs.abstract: The latest Apple and Google models have software that automatically enhances your photos, but you can also take control to get your perfect shot.
docs.snippet: The latest Apple and Google models have software that automatically enhances your photos, but you can also take control to get your perfect shot.
docs.lead_paragraph: It’s getting harder to take a truly bad photo on a good smartphone. Thanks to better lenses, robust processors and integrated computational photography software to process images under the hood, even scenes in low-light, no-flash situations that used to be hopelessly murky can now turn out nicely.

headline.main: Get the Most Out of Your Fancy Smartphone Camera
headline.print_headline: The Quest for That Perfect Shot

docs.abstract: Gary Jones, the United Auto Workers leader until last fall, is accused of embezzlement. A prosecutor spoke of a previous U.S. takeover of a union as a model.
docs.snippet: Gary Jones, the United Auto Workers leader until last fall, is accused of embezzlement. A prosecutor spoke of a previous U.S. takeover of a union as a model.
docs.lead_paragraph: For five years, federal investigators have pieced together a broad pattern of corruption within the United Automobile Workers. They documented the diversion of dues for high living by union officials and found a conspiracy that may have compromised dealings with a leading automaker.

headline.main: U.A.W. Corruption Case Widens as Former Chief Is Charged
headline.print_headline: Former Chief  Now Charged In U.A.W. Case

byline.original: By Noam Scheiber and Neal E. Boudette
